5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING PUBLIC RECORD LAWS RELATING TO THE
6 SUPREME COURT AND THE LEGISLATURE; REQUIRING THE RECORDING OF A CLOSED JUDICIAL
7 DELIBERATION MEETING; PROVIDING FOR THE DISCLOSURE OF JUDICIAL DELIBERATIONS AND
8 CASE INFORMATION AFTER A CASE IS FINAL; PROVIDING THAT LEGISLATIVE BILL DRAFTING FILES
9 ARE PUBLIC RECORDS THAT ARE AVAILABLE ON REQUEST PURSUANT TO MONTANA'S PUBLIC
10 RECORDS LAWS; AMENDING SECTIONS 2-3-203, 2-3-212, AND 2-6-1002, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
11 EFFECTIVE DATE DATES.”
12
13 WHEREAS, Montana has a deeply rooted commitment to the transparency and accountability of
14 government, as demonstrated by the protections offered by the right to know in Article II, section 9, and the
15 right of participation in the operations of government agencies in Article II, section 8, of the Montana
16 Constitution; and
17 WHEREAS, the Montana Constitution has enshrined access to public information in the right to know in
18 Article II, section 9, which states that "No person shall be deprived of the right to examine documents or to
19 observe the deliberations of all public bodies or agencies of state government and its subdivisions, except in
20 cases in which the demand of individual privacy clearly exceeds the merits of public disclosure"; and
21 WHEREAS, these fundamental rights are the foundation on which every Montanan is able to exercise
22 the power to hold elected officials accountable for their actions and decisions; and
23 WHEREAS, in recognition of its commitment to the principles of transparency and accountability, the
24 Montana Legislature has had a long-standing policy of allowing public access to the information collected in
25 legislative bill drafting files; and
26 WHEREAS, THE RIGHT TO KNOW CLAUSE FOUND IN ARTICLE II, SECTION 9, OF THE MONTANA CONSTITUTION
